- 2.0.2 | Feb 23 2026:

  -- New Features --

[New] SYN flood protection: SYNFLOOD chain rate-limits inbound TCP SYN packets
      via iptables limit module; configurable rate/burst thresholds, LOG +
      DROP for excess, dual-stack support (conf.apf, bt.rules, .ca.def)
[New] SMTP outbound blocking: SMTP_BLOCK restricts outbound SMTP (ports 25,
      465, 587) to whitelisted users/groups; root always allowed;
      SMTP_ALLOWUSER/SMTP_ALLOWGROUP exemptions with runtime --gid-owner
      detection; works independently of EGF toggle (conf.apf, cports.common)
[New] Temporary allow/deny with per-entry TTL: apf -ta/-td HOST TTL adds
      time-limited trust entries; supports seconds/minutes/hours/days (300,
      5m, 1h, 7d); automatic cron expiry; list with --templ, flush with
      --tempf (apf, functions.apf, cron.d.apf)
[New] Custom hook scripts: hook_pre.sh/hook_post.sh sourced before/after
      iptables rules; activated by chmod 750; all APF variables available;
      preserved across upgrades (firewall, importconf)
[New] Silent IP blocking: silent_ips.rules drops all traffic to/from listed
      addresses with no logging; IPv4/IPv6 supported; preserved across
      upgrades (firewall, importconf)
[New] Search CLI: apf -g PATTERN searches iptables rules (IPv4/IPv6), ipset
      sets, and trust files; case-insensitive (apf, functions.apf)
[New] Per-port connection limiting via xt_connlimit: IG_TCP_CLIMIT and
      IG_UDP_CLIMIT config variables with port:limit pairs, port range
      support, and VNET per-IP binding (conf.apf, cports.common)
[New] ipset 7-field format: per-list refresh interval and max entry count;
      IPSET_REFRESH global default; per-list interval tracking via
      .ipset.timestamps; backward-compatible auto-migration from 4-field
      and 5-field formats (functions.apf, ipset.rules, conf.apf)

  -- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] lgate_mac(): use $VF_LGATE instead of undefined $LGATE_MAC; gateway
      MAC filtering was non-functional (functions.apf)
[Fix] expirebans(): fix $ip loop variable shadowing global iproute2 path;
      replace unquoted array expansion with IFS read to prevent globbing;
      add date parse error handling; skip ttl= entries (functions.apf)
[Fix] ipset_migrate_rules(): add 5-field (v2.0.1) to 7-field migration;
      5-field entries were silently dropped on upgrade (functions.apf)
[Fix] glob_allow_download()/glob_deny_download(): validate entries with
      valid_host() instead of raw file copy (functions.apf)
[Fix] escape dots in IP addresses used in sed patterns across
      cli_trust_remove(), expirebans(), expire_temp_entries() (functions.apf)
[Fix] importconf: preserve preroute.rules and postroute.rules during
      upgrade; custom ToS/routing rules were silently lost (importconf)
[Fix] importconf: cp -pf for hook scripts to preserve executable permission
      across upgrades (importconf)
[Fix] SMTP_BLK: add chain-exists guard for VNET re-sourcing; add to Docker
      compat flush chain list; warn on empty SMTP_PORTS (cports.common,
      functions.apf)
[Fix] .ca.def preamble: add missing defaults for SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_*,
      DOCKER_COMPAT, IG_ICMPV6_TYPES, EG_ICMPV6_TYPES; prevents empty
      values on upgrade from pre-2.0.1 (.ca.def)
[Fix] silent_ips.rules: validate entries with valid_host() before passing
      to iptables (firewall)
[Fix] conf.apf: correct DOCKER_COMPAT comment to match actual behavior
      (conf.apf)
[Fix] Bash 4.2+ ${var,,}/${var^^} reverted to tr-based case conversion for
      CentOS 6 compatibility (cports.common, internals.conf)

  -- Changes --

[Change] ESTABLISHED,RELATED state tracking moved earlier in INPUT chain;
      established connections now fast-path past VNET, port filtering, and
      logging (firewall)
[Change] Fast load uptime threshold raised from 5 to 10 minutes (apf)
[Change] Consolidate 3 cron files into single cron.d.apf with daily restart,
      hourly ipset refresh, and per-minute temp expiry (cron.d.apf, install.sh)
[Change] ipset batch loading via ipset restore; reduces load time from
      minutes to seconds for large block lists (functions.apf)
[Change] Performance: replace subprocess chains (echo|tr|awk|grep) with bash
      builtins and parameter expansion across all hot paths; eliminate useless
      cat pipes; convert subshell returns to variable-return pattern; cache
      local address lookups (functions.apf, cports.common, bt.rules, firewall,
      vnetgen, main.vnet, sysctl.rules, install.sh, internals.conf)
[Change] Consolidate duplicated code: trust_hosts() unifies allow/deny
      loading; dlist_download() unifies 4 download functions; _icmp_filter()
      unifies 4 ICMP blocks; expand_port() replaces 10 port-range conversions;
      trust_parse_fields() replaces per-entry field parsing; tosroute()
      consolidated from 6 blocks to 1 loop (functions.apf, cports.common)
[Change] Modernize string tests ([ "$x" == "" ] → [ -z "$x" ]) and remove
      unnecessary $(echo $var) wrappers across all files
[Change] VNET: replace fork-heavy parsing with builtins and glob patterns;
      fix ifconfig detection; add variable quoting (main.vnet, vnetgen)
[Change] help(): show all CLI aliases, normalize alignment (functions.apf)
[Change] cl_cports(): reset SMTP and connlimit variables for VNET per-IP
      consistency (functions.apf)
[Change] Drop Ubuntu 22.04 from CI matrix; redundant with 20.04+24.04
      (smoke-test.yml)

  -- Documentation --

[New] FLOW.md/FLOW: standalone order-of-operations document with INPUT chain
      precedence table and fast/full load conditions
[Change] README/README.md: modernize headers; add Quick Start section;
      reorganize feature list; add documentation for connlimit, uid-based
      egress, ICMPv6 types, SMTP blocking, temporary trust, hooks, silent
      IPs, search CLI, and firewall order of operations

  -- Test Suite --

[New] 8 new test files: 21-refactor-regression, 22-uid-egress,
      23-devel-fastload, 24-vnet, 25-connlimit, 26-hook-search-silent,
      27-temp-trust, 28-synflood (398 tests total across 28 files)
[New] Test parallelization: --parallel [N] flag splits across N containers;
      3x speedup (run-tests.sh, Makefile)
